==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Attame
<hw>At*tame"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>atamer</ets>, from Latin. See <er>Attaminate</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To pierce; to attack.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To broach; to begin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And right anon his tale he hath <qex>attamed</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Attaminate</ent>⟦br⟧
